      • apply

        public java.lang.Object apply(java.lang.Object left,
                              Lazy right)
                       throws CarrotException
        Description copied from interface: BinaryOperator
        Applies the binary operator to the given operands.

        Note that the right operand is passed as a Lazy because some operands may not need to evaluate it, depending on the left operand (e.g. boolean `and` and `or` operators).

        Specified by:
        apply in interface BinaryOperator
        Parameters:
        left - The left operand.
        right - The Lazy right operand.
        Returns:
        The result of the operation.
        Throws:
        CarrotException - if there's any error applying the operator.
